args: *sigh* I've had it up to here with all this\nattention. I just need to hide a little until\nall the hubbub dies down.
Urgh, but on the other hand, I came here\nto have a vacation with Elisanne...
I guess I'll have to find someplace we\ncan relax without people hounding us.
Well, well. Ain't she the one who swept\nthis year's contest? Looks like she's off\nsulking by her lonesome. Heh. Lucky me.
Hey there. What's got your goat?
I couldn't help but notice that frown on\nyour beautiful face. You get separated\nfrom your friends?
No. I wanted some alone time, actually.
Aw, where's the fun in that? How's about\nI take you someplace nice instead?
I know a good spot that's perfectly hidden\naway from prying eyes. Heh heh heh!
(I may as well take him up on his offer and\nsee if it's somewhere I can take Elisanne.)
I'd appreciate that. Lead the way.
Here we are. Head right on inside, milady!
Hee hee hee! Kinda your fault for\nblindly following me, lady.
Only because you told me my\nfriends were here!
Did I? Can't say I remember. Ha ha ha!
You are about to be in a world of hurt\nif you don't leave her alone. Back off.
Come on now, don't be like that. I bet\nyou and I could get along reeeal nicely.
What the hell are you talking about?
Oh, y'know! A little of this, a little of that...
Elisanne?! What are you doing here?
I couldn't find you, and then I saw you\nleave with that suspicious-looking man.
I was worried you might've gotten mixed\nup with some smooth-talking pickup\nartist...and I was right.
Men who sweet-talk women into sharing\ntheir company. If it ended there, that'd\nbe one thing...
But among them are vile cowards who\ntry to force women to do things they\ndon't want to doâ€”like these men here.
Now I see what's happening here. We're\ndealing with some grade-A scoundrels.
Perfect. That means I don't have to pull\nmy punches. PREPARE YOURSELVES!
Punishment comes swiftly for the wicked.\nYou'd better learn from this and think on\nwhat you've done.
Thank you for that. You saved me again.
Aaaaagh! There're fiends coming from the\nocean!
Oh, right! You were one of the contestants!
I was. I'm SO grateful for what you did.
The sight of you fighting so brilliantly\nhasn't left my mind since. I'd actually\nhoped I'd see you again.
It's gotta be fate that our paths crossed\nagain, don't you think?
I want nothing more than to be swaddled\nnext to your protective bosom! PLEASE!
I... I'm sorry, but I don't think that's\nsomething I can do.
My heart's already set on someone.\nHer name is Elisanne.
What are you TALKING ABOUT?!\nDon't joke like that, Alex!
Who said it was a joke? I'm serious.
If that's how it's to be...then I wish\nyou two the best. Farewell!
Huh?! No, hey, wait!\nI can't... I mean, she...!
All I said was that I'm not going to be\nprotecting anybody other than you.
My heart is set on it. That's why I can't\npromise to look after anyone else.
Oh. So that's what you meant.\nHonestly...
*sigh* All this excitement has me beat.
Shall we go take a breather?\nI know just the spot.
Sure. And this time, I won't have to worry\nwhere I'm being taken...unlike with certain\nmiscreants.
